{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17628546","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17628546"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:59:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:59:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17226"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17226","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17226"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.03,0.7,0.15,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9916"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69593"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9916","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9916"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17226"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55045"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"524"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5131"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23255"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23261"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23314"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69593","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69593"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EGastric acid secretion has three phases:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECephalic\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGastric\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIntestinal\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe cephalic phase is set into action by the anticipation of food or the taste and smell of food. This phase is mediated through the vagus. In the gastric phase acid is secreted from the gastric parietal cells.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of acid secretion?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sodium-hydrogen ion exchange","Direct secretion of hydrogen chloride molecules","Active transport of hydrogen ions via hydrogen-potassium ATPase pump","Carbonic anhydrase-mediated acid production","Passive diffusion of hydrochloric acid across cell membrane"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EGastric parietal cells secrete hydrochloric acid through \u003Cstrong\u003Eactive transport of hydrogen ions via hydrogen-potassium ATPase pumps\u003C/strong\u003E located in their apical membrane. This pump (also called the proton pump) exchanges hydrogen ions for potassium ions against a concentration gradient, requiring ATP.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect mechanisms can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPassive diffusion of hydrochloric acid\u003C/strong\u003E - Acid secretion requires energy and cannot occur through passive processes due to the large concentration gradient\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESodium-hydrogen ion exchange\u003C/strong\u003E - While this occurs in other tissues, gastric acid secretion specifically uses potassium as the counter-ion\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarbonic anhydrase-mediated acid production\u003C/strong\u003E - While carbonic anhydrase is involved in generating hydrogen ions intracellularly, it is not the primary secretory mechanism\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect secretion of hydrogen chloride molecules\u003C/strong\u003E - Hydrogen and chloride ions are secreted separately, not as intact HCl molecules\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe hydrogen-potassium ATPase pump is the final common pathway for acid secretion and is the target of proton pump inhibitor medications used to treat acid-related disorders.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gastric parietal cells secrete hydrochloric acid via hydrogen-potassium ATPase pumps in their apical membrane.","Histamine, acetylcholine, and gastrin are the main stimulants of gastric acid secretion.","Proton pump inhibitors block the hydrogen-potassium ATPase pump to reduce acid secretion."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Boron W. F., Boulpaep E. L. Medical Physiology. (3rd edition). US. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2017."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55045"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17226"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55045","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55045"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-12T11:13:07+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-12T11:19:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9916"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69593"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"typ